##DESCRIPTION
##  calculate the limit of a piecewise defined function
##ENDDESCRIPTION

##Tagged by ynw2d

## DBsubject(Calculus - single variable)
## DBchapter(Limits and continuity)
## DBsection(Infinite limits and vertical asymptotes)
## Date(6/3/2002)
## Level(2)
## MO(1)
## TitleText1('Calculus: Early Transcendentals')
## AuthorText1('Stewart')
## EditionText1('6')
## Section1('2.3')
## Problem1('44')
## KEYWORDS('Calculus','Limit', 'Piecewise','limits','piecewise function')


DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
#  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

Context('Numeric');

$m = random(2,4,1);
$x = random(1,6,1);
$a = random(1,9,1);
$b = random(0,5,1)+$m*$x;

BEGIN_TEXT
$BR
Let \(f(x) =
            \begin{cases}
              -\frac{$a}{x+$x}, &\text{if}\ x< -$x\\
              $m x+$b, &\text{if}\ x> -$x
              \end{cases}
\)
$BR
Calculate the following limits.  If the limit doesn't exist but it makes sense to call it \(\infty\) enter $BBOLD Infinity $EBOLD, for \(-\infty\) enter $BBOLD -Infinity $EBOLD; in other cases where the limit does not exist enter $BBOLD DNE $EBOLD. 
$BR
$BR
\( \displaystyle{\lim_{x\to -$x^-}f(x)=} \) \{ans_rule(15)\}
END_TEXT

#$ans1 = Compute("DNE");
$ans1 = Infinity;
ANS($ans1->cmp);

BEGIN_TEXT
$BR
\( \displaystyle{\lim_{x\to -$x^+}f(x)=} \) \{ans_rule(15)\}
END_TEXT

$ans2 = Compute("-$m*$x+$b");
ANS($ans2->cmp);

BEGIN_TEXT
$BR
\( \displaystyle{\lim_{x\to -$x}f(x)=} \) \{ans_rule(15)\}
END_TEXT

$ans3 = Compute("DNE");
ANS($ans3->cmp);

ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
